1. Definition
Number.isInteger(value) returns true if value is of the Number type and is a mathematical integer (no fractional part), otherwise false.

2. Normalised extract (implementation-ready)
- Signature: Number.isInteger(value) -> boolean
- Implementation pattern (spec-compliant):
  - return typeof value === 'number' && isFinite(value) && Math.floor(value) === value
- Behavior for special values:
  - NaN, Infinity, -Infinity -> false
  - Non-number types -> false (no coercion)

3. Edge cases and spec details
- Large integers (beyond Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER) that are mathematically integers still return true if value is a number with zero fractional part, but integer precision may be unreliable for equality operations.
- Use Number.isSafeInteger to additionally require value to be within safe integer range.

4. Reference details (signature)
- Exact signature: Number.isInteger(value: any) : boolean
- Polyfill (ES5):
  Number.isInteger = Number.isInteger || function(value) {
    return typeof value === 'number' && isFinite(value) && Math.floor(value) === value;
  }

